<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>AWESOME message man! Well said. NT</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Meteo">Meteo</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:05 p.m. 2/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> AWESOME message man! Well said. NT<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1989" TARGET=_self>A little rant</A> (Benign)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> I hear alot of talk about this guild or that guild being a bunch

<BR>&gt; of PKing macroing fools in UO and that is the only reason they
<BR>&gt; where good. Let me tell you something, everyone(PK or not)
<BR>&gt; should have been macroing in UO. Most people did, and when the
<BR>&gt; fighting was done the person who won was the better player. All
<BR>&gt; that happened was the guilds used what resources where available
<BR>&gt; to them to make them the best and then fought about it. The same
<BR>&gt; thing is going to happen in EQ. I am already hearing the same
<BR>&gt; type of excuses too.(They play 24/7, he was higher level than
<BR>&gt; me, he used DOT spells which are illegal, he killed me after I
<BR>&gt; fought a monster, I was AFK, etc., etc., etc.) I don't get it at
<BR>&gt; all. You should know what the PvP server is. Call it a
<BR>&gt; role-playing server, but you are just fooling yourself. Say it
<BR>&gt; is supposed to be a role-playing server and you are correct, but
<BR>&gt; it ain't gonna be.
<P>&gt; The PvP server is for competition and adaption. The better PK
<BR>&gt; guilds realize this(as well as the fact that a good player at
<BR>&gt; one game will be a good player at another game) and use whatever
<BR>&gt; resources are available to make them the best for PvP then prove
<BR>&gt; it. This is no secret, and you can do the same, or you can
<BR>&gt; leave.
<P>&gt; They are already starting to make limitations which turned UO
<BR>&gt; into a PvP nightmare(I mean the for PKers, not the non-PvP
<BR>&gt; people on the PvP server). I personally believe whatever rules
<BR>&gt; are in place now should stay the same, adapt or leave. I like
<BR>&gt; the PvP combat. I know right now that the best PvPers are
<BR>&gt; Druids, Wizards, and Necros. So naturally I will be one of
<BR>&gt; those. You(not you necessarily nitpickers) say,"Well I
<BR>&gt; wanna be a PvP warrior so make them more powerful!". Too
<BR>&gt; bad, if you want to be a warrior just realize that they are not
<BR>&gt; the greatest for PvP, and either be one anyways and avoid PvP,
<BR>&gt; or hunt in groups, or do something(JUST ADAPT). The more I logon
<BR>&gt; to see that the game has some new dumbass "feature"
<BR>&gt; added the more upset I get. I don't mind adapting to a game, but
<BR>&gt; I don't like adapting every single day.
<P>&gt; P.S. My UO example that doesn't pertain at all to EQ, yet... I
<BR>&gt; was a mage fireballing everyone in site. The next day people
<BR>&gt; without armor where hardly affected by fireballs so I got my
<BR>&gt; halberding skill up making me a mage/warrior. The next day
<BR>&gt; Archers become insanely more powerful than any other type and
<BR>&gt; people that had an inside source murdered me with their archers.
<BR>&gt; So, naturally, I made a char and worked that archery skill up
<BR>&gt; only to find that when I was finally ready to do some killing
<BR>&gt; that archers suck again. This wasn't actually a day by day
<BR>&gt; experience, but some of you may remember these events. I just
<BR>&gt; hope Verant doesn't continually listen to people's suggestions
<BR>&gt; to make the game "more balanced" and
<BR>&gt; "better". I like the fact that some classes are better
<BR>&gt; for PvE, PvP, Solo and other such things. You should know what
<BR>&gt; you are getting yourself into, please don't whine when you get
<BR>&gt; there.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
